<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF96FF85FF7EFE87FECCFD18" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" type="description">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF96FF85FF7EFE87FB08FDA4" blockId="23.[136,1452,338,1229]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FF7EFE87FEEBFE8C" bold="true" box="[136,284,338,364]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Description:</emphasis>
—Stem and leaf scales present. Leaf bases connate. Lingulate leaves very long and narrow, 0.7–22.0 mm long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FF2CFEA3FE94FE71" box="[218,355,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
wide; expanded submerged or floating leaves narrowly elliptic, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FBB6FEA3FB3EFE71" box="[1088,1225,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.95" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="4.95" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="4.4">4.4–5.5 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FAD5FEA3FA5BFE71" box="[1315,1452,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="1.95" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2.3 mm</quantity>
wide; venation simple or occasionally branched with veins between central and secondary veins, petiole 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FAD2FE4FFA5BFE55" box="[1316,1452,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="4.85" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="3.2">3.2–6.5 mm</quantity>
long; leaves of terrestrial plants unknown. Flowers solitary. Bracts strongly falcate, caducous, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FB6AFE6BFAD5FE39" box="[1180,1314,446,473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="1.65" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.8 mm</quantity>
long. Styles erect or sub-divergent 2.3–8.0 mm long. Filament erect 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FCF6FE37FC70FE1D" box="[768,903,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.65" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="4.65" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="3.8">3.8–5.5 mm</quantity>
long; anthers, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FBC6FE37FB71FE1D" box="[1072,1158,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FB29FE37FA90FE1D" box="[1247,1383,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.499999999999999" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="0.6499999999999999" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.7 mm</quantity>
wide, number of locules unknown; pollen yellow. Fruits subsessile or very shortly pedicellate, as high as or slightly higher than wide, blackish when mature, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FDF1FDFFFD79FDA5" box="[519,654,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.6 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FD13FDFFFC9BFDA5" box="[741,876,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.4 mm</quantity>
wide, narrowly winged throughout.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF96FF85FF4BFD9BFE2FFD88" blockId="23.[136,1452,338,1229]" box="[189,472,590,616]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FF4BFD9BFEAEFD88" bold="true" box="[189,345,590,616]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Illustrations:</emphasis>
— 
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF96FF85FE81FD9BFE23FD88" box="[375,468,590,616]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,190,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-15@17.[151,1436,190,1889]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Fruits of Callitriche in Oceania and Australasia: a—C. heterophylla, b—C. insularis, c—C. muelleri, d—C. palustris, e—C. papuana, f—C. peploides, g—C. petriei, h—C. platycarpa, i—C. sonderi, j—C. stagnalis, k—C. umbonata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577553/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10e</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF96FF85FF4BFDA7FECCFD18" blockId="23.[136,1452,338,1229]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FF4BFDA7FEA1FD6C" bold="true" box="[189,342,626,652]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FE84FDA6FE04FD6C" authorityName="Merrill &amp; Perry" authorityYear="1941" box="[370,499,627,653]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papuana">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FE84FDA6FE04FD6C" box="[370,499,627,653]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">C. papuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FC89FDA7FBA7FD6C" box="[895,1104,626,652]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FC89FDA7FC0FFD6C" box="[895,1016,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the region by the fruit which are narrowly winged, higher than wide and blackish when mature, combined with the solitary flowers and large bracts. Fruits of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FF05FD6EFE69FD34" authorityName="Mason" authorityYear="1959" box="[243,414,698,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aucklandica">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FF05FD6EFE69FD34" box="[243,414,698,725]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">C. aucklandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be considered similar but are typically wider than high, while its vegetative parts are typically fleshy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF96FF8AFF4BFCD7FC07FE8C" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="267" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF96FF85FF4BFCD7FAB5FCA0" blockId="23.[136,1452,338,1229]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FF4BFCD7FEAEFCFC" bold="true" box="[189,345,770,796]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Native. 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FE39FCD7FD45FCFC" authorityName="Merrill &amp; Perry" authorityYear="1941" box="[463,690,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papuana">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FE39FCD7FD45FCFC" box="[463,690,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Callitriche papuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from a few specimens collected in the highlands of New 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF96FF85FF7EFCF3FF2BFCA0" box="[136,220,806,832]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, from Lake Habbema in West Papua, to Mount Victoria near Port Moresby in New 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF96FF85FB74FCF3FB24FCA0" box="[1154,1235,806,832]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Guinea</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF96FF85FB14FCF3FAC2FCA0" box="[1250,1333,806,832]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="23.[136,229,1863,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-446@23.[267,1319,1253,1839]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 14. The distribution of confirmed specimens of C. papuana" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580493/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF96FF85FF4BFC9FFC08FBF8" blockId="23.[136,1452,338,1229]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FF4BFC9FFE3EFC84" bold="true" box="[189,457,842,868]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Habitats and Ecology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FE13FC9EFD9FFC84" authorityName="Merrill &amp; Perry" authorityYear="1941" box="[485,616,843,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papuana">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FE13FC9EFD9FFC84" box="[485,616,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">C. papuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been described as occurring in water with pH between 6.50 and 7.50, including in the shallow, marginal waters of a lake surrounded by forest. Populations determined as 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FB03FCBAFA8EFC68" authorityName="von Linne" authorityYear="1753" box="[1269,1401,878,905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FB03FCBAFA8EFC68" box="[1269,1401,878,905]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">C. palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but probably this species have been reported from pools, the outflow stream from a lake and a small bog lake at high altitude, with a thick growth of submerged 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FD9BFC63FB8EFC30" authority="(von Linne) R. Br. (1810: 221)" authorityName="R. Br." authorityPageNumber="221" authorityYear="1810" baseAuthorityName="von Linne" box="[621,1145,950,977]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Isolepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fluitans">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FD9BFC63FCE8FC30" box="[621,799,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Isolepis fluitans</emphasis>
(von Linné) R.Br. (1810: 221)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FB46FC62FF56FC15" authority="Link (1820: 5)" authorityName="Link" authorityPageNumber="5" authorityYear="1820" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Zygnemataceae" genus="Spirogyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FB46FC62FAE8FC31" box="[1200,1311,951,977]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Spirogyra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF96FF85FAD0FC63FF56FC15" author="Link, H. F." pageId="23" pageNumber="266" refId="ref33868" refString="Link, H. F. (1820) Epistola de algis aquaticis, in genera disponendis. In Nees, C. G. Horae physicae Berolinenses collectae ex symbolis virorum doctorum. Adolphi Marcus, Bonn." type="book" year="1820">Link (1820: 5)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, surrounded by fringe of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FE3AFC0EFC58FC14" authority="Kunth (1837: 417)" authorityName="Kunth" authorityPageNumber="417" authorityYear="1837" box="[460,943,986,1013]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gaudichaudiana">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FE3AFC0EFD38FC14" box="[460,719,986,1013]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Carex gaudichaudiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF96FF85FD2FFC0FFC58FC14" author="Kunth, C. S." box="[729,943,986,1012]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" refId="ref32620" refString="Kunth, C. S. (1837) Enumeratio Plantarum Omnium Hucusque Cognitarum, Secundum Familias Naturales Disposita, Adjectis Characteribus, Differntiis et Synonymis. Stuttgart and Tubingen, Germany. 543 pp." type="book" year="1837">Kunth (1837: 417)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
fen which is surrounded in turn by 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FAA0FC0FFF27FBF8" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carpha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpina">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FAA0FC0FFF27FBF8" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Carpha alpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fen (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF96FF85FEFFFC2BFE4CFBF9" author="Hoogland RD" box="[265,443,1022,1049]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" pagination="20 - 238" refId="ref31948" refString="Hoogland RD. (1958) The alpine flora of Mount Wilhelm (New Guinea). Blumea Suppl. 4: 20 - 238." type="journal article" year="1958">Hoogland 1958</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF96FF85FE30FC2BFD2CFBF9" author="Wade, L. K. &amp; McVean, D. N." box="[454,731,1022,1049]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" refId="ref37367" refString="Wade, L. K. &amp; McVean, D. N. (1969) Mt Wilhem Studies I. The alpine and subalpine vegetation. Biogeography and Geomorphology Series 1, Australian National University, Canberra, Australia. 225 pp." type="book" year="1969">Wade and McVean 1969</bibRefCitation>
). 
<quantity id="1822C293FF96FF85FD19FC2BFC7DFBF9" box="[751,906,1022,1049]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1625" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="2.225" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" unit="m" value="3162.5" valueMax="4100.0" valueMin="2225.0">2225–4100 m</quantity>
elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF96FF85FF4BFBF7FCE4FB80" blockId="23.[136,1452,338,1229]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FF4BFBF7FE4FFBDC" bold="true" box="[189,440,1058,1084]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
—The information available is not adequate to assess the conservation status of the species and it is therefore classed as Data Deficient (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF96FF85FD8AFB93FCF0FB80" author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[636,775,1094,1120]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" refId="ref32363" refString="IUCN (2012). IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. 2 nd ed. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK. 32 pp" type="book" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF96FF85FF4BFBBFFE16FB2C" blockId="23.[136,1452,338,1229]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FF4BFBBFFEFEFB64" bold="true" box="[189,265,1130,1156]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FED0FBBEFE5CFB64" authorityName="Merrill &amp; Perry" authorityYear="1941" box="[294,427,1131,1157]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papuana">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FED0FBBEFE5CFB64" box="[294,427,1131,1157]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">C. papuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely poorly known, with no records since 1980. As with many other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FAC4FBBFFF2EFB48" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FAC4FBBFFA5CFB64" box="[1330,1451,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the region, there is a need for fieldwork to assess its current conservation status and collect accurate information on its distribution.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8BA53FFEFF96FF85FF7EF892FCD1F8BD" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580493" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6580493" box="[136,806,1863,1885]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580493/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" startId="23.[136,229,1863,1885]" targetBox="[282,1311,1266,1827]" targetPageId="23">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF96FF85FF7EF892FCD1F8BD" blockId="23.[136,806,1863,1885]" box="[136,806,1863,1885]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF96FF85FF7EF892FEF4F8BC" bold="true" box="[136,259,1863,1885]" pageId="23" pageNumber="266">FIGURE 14</emphasis>
. The distribution of confirmed specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF96FF85FD40F89DFCD1F8BD" authorityName="Merrill &amp; Perry" authorityYear="1941" box="[694,806,1864,1885]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="266" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papuana">C. papuana</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</caption>
